  "texts": [
    "For Blair and Cowley (2003), \"what human bodies and voices do together affect how we conceptualize our encultured worlds\" and is microcognitive -it induces change in a person (p. 132).",
    "Through languaging, people constantly draw on past engagements to bring forth future actions.",
    "The multiscalarity aspect of language illuminates how people incorporate and build on the movements of others as they continuously integrate slower temporal scales that allow them to hear utterance-activity as similar patterns foot_2 (Cowley 2011b; van den Herik 2017).",
    "Thus, from the languaging perspective, people do not 'use' words; they draw on world-side events and happenings (Cowley 2011b).",
    "Acknowledging linguistic embodiment (Cowley 2014) gives ways to investigate human presencing, moving away from an object-like approach to language."
  ],
